                         PLOT                          
                                                     
                                                             
           

          A uniquely delicate and moving road movie, Barking Water uses the 
          weathered and beautiful backdrop of rural Oklahoma to tell the story 
          of Frankie (Richard Ray Whitman), a proud Native American attempting 
          to reconnect with his estranged family. Released from the hospital, 
          but still very ill, he hits the road with his ex-lover Irene 
          (Casey Camp-Horinek), who acts as Frankie's nurse but refuses to offer 
          forgiveness for his past indiscretions. But the journey really begins 
          as they travel through the sun-dappled Oklahoman country to reunite 
          with Frankie's daughter and grandchild, encountering various eccentric 
          personalities, from motor-mouthed nephews to a philosophical pot-smoking 
          loner, along the way.
